b'\xe2\x80\x9cAs we see widespread protests against racial injustices, I am reminded how #Pride first evolved from a protest, the \xf0\x9d\x97\xa6\xf0\x9d\x98\x81\xf0\x9d\x97\xbc\xf0\x9d\x97\xbb\xf0\x9d\x97\xb2\xf0\x9d\x98\x84\xf0\x9d\x97\xae\xf0\x9d\x97\xb9\xf0\x9d\x97\xb9 \xf0\x9d\x97\xa5\xf0\x9d\x97\xb6\xf0\x9d\x97\xbc\xf0\x9d\x98\x81\xf0\x9d\x98\x80. It began because two brave transgender women of color \xe2\x80\x94 \xf0\x9d\x97\xa0\xf0\x9d\x97\xae\xf0\x9d\x97\xbf\xf0\x9d\x98\x80\xf0\x9d\x97\xb5\xf0\x9d\x97\xae \xf0\x9d\x97\xa3. \xf0\x9d\x97\x9d\xf0\x9d\x97\xbc\xf0\x9d\x97\xb5\xf0\x9d\x97\xbb\xf0\x9d\x98\x80\xf0\x9d\x97\xbc\xf0\x9d\x97\xbb and \xf0\x9d\x97\xa6\xf0\x9d\x98\x86\xf0\x9d\x97\xb9\xf0\x9d\x98\x83\xf0\x9d\x97\xb6\xf0\x9d\x97\xae \xf0\x9d\x97\xa5\xf0\x9d\x97\xb6\xf0\x9d\x98\x83\xf0\x9d\x97\xb2\xf0\x9d\x97\xbf\xf0\x9d\x97\xae \xe2\x80\x94 stood their ground to fight for justice and equality. If it wasn\xe2\x80\x99t for them, I wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t have the rights I have today.\xe2\x80\x9d :rainbow:\n\xe2\x80\x94 \xf0\x9d\x97\x9a\xf0\x9d\x97\xb6\xf0\x9d\x97\xbb\xf0\x9d\x97\xbc \xf0\x9d\x97\xa5\xf0\x9d\x97\xae\xf0\x9d\x97\xba\xf0\x9d\x97\xbc\xf0\x9d\x98\x80, Senior Manager of Equality Programs at Salesforce and Co-Founder and Advisor to Outforce, reminds us, \xe2\x80\x9cDuring Pride Month and every month, think about how we can intentionally stand up for what\xe2\x80\x99s right. I encourage you to do your part \xe2\x80\x94 whether it\xe2\x80\x99s joining an ERG, educating yourself, or being an active ally.\xe2\x80\x9d\nLearn more and read Gino\xe2\x80\x99s full blog post at the link in bio. :link:'
